Isle of the Mighty

Edit on GitHub

Overview

UnlockClear Cavern of Suiryu.
EntranceShukuba Beach (Check boats near dock)
Floors50F / 99F (Sacred Tree)
Bring ItemsYesStairsAscending
CompanionsNoRoamersNo
Rescues3Starting LevelLv1
Starting ItemLarge Onigiri
UnidentifiedAll categories
ShopsYesMonster HousesYes (Regular, Sudden, Special)
BehemothsYesWishing ShrinesYes
Kron's ChallengeYesFever TimeYes
Initial Enemies6~16Spawn Rate25 Turns
Wind (1st Gust)1200 TurnsRewardHunky-dory Shield (Gold)

Postgame dungeon that can be unlocked after clearing Cavern of Suiryu.
It's the most challenging dungeon among the ones where the player is allowed to bring items,
and it features a number of powerful Lv3~4 monsters that don't naturally appear in other dungeons.
Strong equipment is mandatory, and you'll also want runes and bracelets to counter specific enemies.
Items like Golden Pickaxe, Epic Hammer, and Expulsion Scroll can rarely be found in shops on 48-49F.
If you want to complete the notebook, you're likely going to have to play this dungeon multiple times.

Strategy

General

Floor numbers that are a multiple of 10 don't have dark hallways, and often have buried items.
The only items that can be generated on the ground on 25F are Gitan bags worth 1000G each.

Rare Items

Expulsion Scroll, Golden Pickaxe, and Epic Hammer have a chance to appear in shops only on 48-49F.
These 3 items are exceptionally rare, so expect to run the dungeon multiple times before you find them.
Some players have had to complete the dungeon 30+ times before they found even 1 Golden Pickaxe.
※ Accurate Sword can't be found in this dungeon, but the Accurate rune can appear on sacred items here.

Rare items and runes that can appear here:

  • Weapons / Shields
    • Golden Pickaxe (48-49F), Epic Hammer (48-49F), Bodhi Shield.
  • Bracelets / Other
    • Clairvoyant Bracelet, Sure-aim Bracelet, Expulsion Scroll (48-49F).
  • Runes
    • Accurate, Max Trap Bust, Max Wall Dig, Anti-Behemoth, Thunderbolt.

Equipment

Any weapon and shield with +99 upgrade value should be fine, even if it doesn't have high base stats.
The optimal sets are either Kabura Sutegi + Rasen Fuuma, or Yamanba's Cleaver + Yamanba's Potlid.
It's important to be at 10+ strength to be able to equip a 2nd bracelet, so don't forget 2 Strength Grass
if you're not using the Yamanba's Cleaver + Yamanba's Potlid equipment set.

Weapon Runes

  • Rustproof, HP+15, HP+20
    • Not exactly essential, but nice to have.
  • Frontal Attack, Side Attack
    • Runes to boost your attack range.
  • Critical, Swift Strikes, Anti-Aquatic, Anti-Beast, Anti-Dragon, Anti-Draining, Anti-Cyclops
    • Runes to boost your damage output.
  • Healing
    • Restore HP equal to 10% of damage dealt.
  • Peach Bun
    • Makes hunger a non-issue.
  • Accurate, Max Wall Dig
    • Can be found on sacred items within Isle of the Mighty.

Shield Runes

  • Sating, Rustproof, HP+15, HP+20
    • Not exactly essential, but nice to have.
  • Magic Cancel or Magic Reflect
    • Skull Lord (28-39F).
  • Anti-Dragon, Anti-Blast
    • Abyss Dragon (45-50F), Adamant Tank (5-8F), Steadfast Tank (15-18F), etc.
  • Projectileproof, Nigiriproof, Hypnosisproof, Walrusproof, Hatproof
    • Magicwalrus (11-18F), Frenzy Radish (3-9F), Nigiri Honcho (15-18F), Ultra Gazer (28-39F), etc.

Bracelets

Monster-find Bracelet / Clairvoyant Bracelet
Check for incoming enemies before you're in range of Frenzy Radish, Porkon, Nimble Knave, etc.

Item-find Bracelet / Clairvoyant Bracelet
Locate items buried in wall tiles, which can be collected using a Collection Scroll.

Wallpass Bracelet
Safely defeat trickier enemies like Mudder, Swordmaster, and Cursenior from inside a wall.
Also helps with avoiding Behemoths and entering buried shops, but watch your HP.
The easiest place to obtain this bracelet is Training Path of Shopping.

Affixing Bracelet
Counters Lv3-4 Field Knaves (1-6F) and Swordmaster (45-50F).

Rustproof Bracelet / Cursebreak Bracelet
Counters Mudster (19-27F), Mudder (19-27F), and Cursenior (19-27F).

Cleansing Bracelet
Counters Demon Scorpion (28-39F), which can lower your Max Strength by 2.

Trapper's Bracelet
Floor-exiting Traps are somewhat common, so this lets you descend through the dungeon faster.

Other Items

Eradication Scroll
Mainly thrown at monster families that can't be countered using shield runes or bracelets.
Frenzy Radish (3-9F), Polygon Stunna (28-39F), and Abyss Dragon (45-50F) are the popular targets.

Blank Scroll
Use it as an Eradication Scroll, Wall-less Scroll, Collection Scroll, etc.
The easiest place to obtain these scrolls is Domain of Staves and Scrolls.

Sumo Onigiri
Mainly used alongside the Peach Bun weapon rune to maintain Sumo status and avoid traps.
Equip 2 Bellyshrink Bracelets before eating it to raise Max Fullness to 200 if desired.

Strength Grass / Special Onigiri / Rejuvenation Pot
Items needed to raise Max Strength to 10 and maintain the ability to equip 2 bracelets.

Revival Grass
Bring multiple of these grasses in case something goes wrong.

Porky's Rock / Evasive Incense
Used to counter Behemoth Monsters, which can include Sleep Radish and Frenzy Radish.

Floor Guide

1F

Lv3 monsters appear right away, so don't forget to equip your weapon and shield before entering.
Popdillo (1-4F) deals 15 damage with its ability, so it can one-shot you at Lv1 if you don't have HP+X runes.
To avoid item loss, either throw an Eradication Scroll at Bag Knave or keep an Affixing Bracelet equipped.
It's best to reach Lv20 before descending to 2F so that you regenerate 3 HP per turn.

2-10F

Recommended to throw an Eradication Scroll at either a Ghost Radish or Field Knave family monster,
with the preference going towards Field Knave if you don't have an Affixing Bracelet.

2-7F - Sleep Radish (135 HP, 47 atk) throws Sedating Grass (or Poison Grass) within a 3 tile radius.
3-9F - Frenzy Radish (195 HP, 57 atk) throws Berserk Seed (or Poison Grass) within a 5 tile radius.
4-6F - Nimble Knave (145 HP, 50 atk) has Swift 1 action speed and knocks away inventory items.
5-8F - Adamant Tank (100 HP, 60 atk) has Swift 1 action speed and fires 40 damage cannonballs.
5-10F - Porkon (150 HP, 75 atk) throws Porky's Rocks which deal 20 damage within a 8 tile radius.
5-10F - Vexing Kappa (175 HP, 49 atk) throws items it finds on the ground within a 10 tile radius.

11-18F

Beware of Magicwalrus (11-18F) and Nigiri Honcho (15-18F) if you have Morphed status,
since equipment abilities and runes are nullified during a monster transformation.

11-14F - Atrocious Kappa (275 HP, 59 atk) throws items it finds on the ground from anywhere on the floor.
15-18F - Steadfast Tank (105 HP, 80 atk) has Swift 2 action speed and fires 50 damage cannonballs.
15-18F - Porgon (200 HP, 85 atk) throws Porky's Rocks which deal 20 damage within a 10 tile radius.

19-27F

Either keep a Wallpass Bracelet equipped, or alternate Cursebreak and Rustproof bracelets.

19-27F - Cursenior (205 HP, 65 atk) curses 2 items, but prioritizes equipped items first.
19-27F - Mudster (140 HP, 35 atk) lowers upgrade value by 1, or erases 1 rune.
19-27F - Mudder (145 HP, 45 atk) lowers upgrade value by 2, or erases 1 rune.

28-39F

Ultra Gazer (28-39F) and Skull Lord (28-39F) are a non-issue if you have shield runes to counter them.
Keep a Cleansing Bracelet equipped and throw an Eradication Scroll at Polygon Stunna if you're worried.

28-39F - Demon Scorpion (295 HP, 73 atk) lowers Max Strength by 2 when adjacent.
28-39F - Polygon Stunna (229 HP, 50 atk) lowers Max Fullness by 10 when adjacent.
28-39F - Showpin (250 HP, 55 atk) summons up to 3 new monsters at once.

40-44F

Lv3-4 Mamels, Lv4 ninjas, and Lv4 monks are the only monsters that appear here.
You shouldn't have any difficulties with strong equipment.

45-50F

The safest strategy is to equip an Affixing Bracelet and throw an Eradication Scroll at Abyss Dragon.
Shops on 48-49F have a chance of having extremely rare items like Expulsion Scroll (3000G) for sale,
and 49F in particular often generates a dungeon shop, so don't rush past these floors.

45-50F - Abyss Dragon (300 HP, 90 atk) breathes a 40 damage flame from anywhere on the floor.
45-50F - Swordmaster (250 HP, 77 atk) disarms your equipped weapon, shield, or bracelet.

Monsters

See Monsters for individual monster details.

  • F - Dark hallways
  • S - Shop is possible
  • H - Monster House is possible
  • G - Golden Egg Thing is possible
  • B - Behemoth Monsters are possible
